#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.65"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.65:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:0.2"
msgid "7. Migajālavagga "
msgstr "7. With Migajāla "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 65. Paṭhamasamiddhimārapañhāsutta → samidhimārapañhasuttaṃ (bj) | samiddhi 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.65:0.3"
msgid "65. Paṭhamasamiddhimārapañhāsutta "
msgstr "65. Samiddhi’s Question About Māra "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn35.65:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

msgctxt "sn35.65:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā samiddhi yena bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "Then Venerable Samiddhi went up to the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn35.65:1.3"
msgid "bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:1.4"
msgid "“‘māro, māro’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of this thing called ‘Māra’. "

# NOTE: The use of pannatti in this and succeeding suttas is unique. See parallel at SA 230, which has 世間者，云何名世間
msgctxt "sn35.65:1.5"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, māro vā assa mārapaññatti vā”ti? "
msgstr "How do we define Māra or what is known as Māra?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.39, sc2
msgctxt "sn35.65:2.1"
msgid "“Yattha kho, samiddhi, atthi cakkhu, atthi rūpā, atthi cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, atthi cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, atthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā. "
msgstr "“Samiddhi, where there is the eye, sights, eye consciousness, and phenomena to be known by eye consciousness, there is Māra or what is known as Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:2.2"
msgid "Atthi sotaṃ, atthi saddā, atthi sotaviññāṇaṃ, atthi sotaviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, atthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā. "
msgstr "Where there is the ear, sounds, ear consciousness, and phenomena to be known by ear consciousness, there is Māra or what is known as Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:2.3"
msgid "Atthi ghānaṃ, atthi gandhā, atthi ghānaviññāṇaṃ, atthi ghānaviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, atthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā. "
msgstr "Where there is the nose, smells, nose consciousness, and phenomena to be known by nose consciousness, there is Māra or what is known as Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:2.4"
msgid "Atthi jivhā, atthi rasā, atthi jivhāviññāṇaṃ, atthi jivhāviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, atthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā. "
msgstr "Where there is the tongue, tastes, tongue consciousness, and phenomena to be known by tongue consciousness, there is Māra or what is known as Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:2.5"
msgid "Atthi kāyo, atthi phoṭṭhabbā, atthi kāyaviññāṇaṃ, atthi kāyaviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, atthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā. "
msgstr "Where there is the body, touches, body consciousness, and phenomena to be known by body consciousness, there is Māra or what is known as Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:2.6"
msgid "Atthi mano, atthi dhammā, atthi manoviññāṇaṃ, atthi manoviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, atthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā. "
msgstr "Where there is the mind, thoughts, mind consciousness, and phenomena to be known by mind consciousness, there is Māra or what is known as Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.65:3.1"
msgid "Yattha ca kho, samiddhi, natthi cakkhu, natthi rūpā, natthi cakkhuviññāṇaṃ, natthi cakkhuviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, natthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā. "
msgstr "Where there is no eye, no sights, no eye consciousness, and no phenomena to be known by eye consciousness, there is no Māra or what is known as Māra. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:3.2"
msgid "Natthi sotaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Where there is no ear … "

msgctxt "sn35.65:3.3"
msgid "natthi ghānaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "no nose … "

msgctxt "sn35.65:3.4"
msgid "natthi jivhā, natthi rasā, natthi jivhāviññāṇaṃ, natthi jivhāviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, natthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā. "
msgstr "no tongue … "

msgctxt "sn35.65:3.5"
msgid "Natthi kāyo … pe …. "
msgstr "no body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.65:3.6"
msgid "Natthi mano, natthi dhammā, natthi manoviññāṇaṃ, natthi manoviññāṇaviññātabbā dhammā, natthi tattha māro vā mārapaññatti vā”ti. "
msgstr "Where there is no mind, no thoughts, no mind consciousness, and no phenomena to be known by mind consciousness, there is no Māra or what is known as Māra.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.65:3.7"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

